    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.29.1-2_0001b" />
                <note type="curatorial">112-2</note>
              
              <opener>
                <dateline>Skyrim, 7-28-'60</dateline>
                
                <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
              </opener>
                <p>Upon reaching home I wrote Bower at once, addressing him at the University Club. I hope the letter reached him. Also, I wrote to Martha and Beverly, but carefully addressed the letter to 1138 22nd Ave, East, <hi rend="underline">Columbia</hi>!! After long search, the postal authorities returned the letter to me. Now that you will soon be at home with Stewart, I'm writing you, as you see.</p>
                
                <p>Need I tell you how
                
                <fw type="curatorial">1</fw>
                    
                    <note type="authorial">Just rec'd a dear note from Bower</note>
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.29.1-2_0001a"/>
                    <note type="curatorial">Aly Collection</note>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    miserable I was in your House of Happiness? Poor company, almost nothing to eat or drink, only two beds to sleep in, and neither of those full-size!! Just the same, thanks dear lady, for all your goodness. (I was <hi rend="italic">not</hi> miserable! The <hi rend="italic">very idea</hi>! <hi rend="underline">Who</hi> ever <hi rend="italic">said</hi> <hi rend="underline">such a thing</hi>?!)</p>
               
                <p>I've been running after horses and sleeping on hay! Feel tired but reasonably happy.</p>
                
                
            </div1>
            
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.29.1-2_0002a"/>
                
                <ab type="return">
                John Neihardt
                Route 7
                <hi rend="underline">Columbia</hi>, Mo.
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">COLUMIA, MO JUL 2<unclear/> 4-PM 1960</ab>
                    <note type="authorial">========
                    Air <hi rend="italic">Mail</hi></note>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>7 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>US <unclear cert="high">AIR</unclear> MAIL 7Â¢</p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                <addrLine>Dr. Lucile Aly,</addrLine>
                <addrLine>1138 22nd Ave., East,</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Eugene,</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Oregon.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
                <note type="authorial">(over)</note>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.29.1-2_0002b"/>
                
                <note type="authorial">Dear Bower: Books arrived in good condition. That is a dear letter from you. John</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">2</fw>
            </div1>
